    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n61" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγείρω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἤγειρα</span>, pass. pf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγήγερμαι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠγέρθην</span>,
          3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄγερθεν</span>, mid. 2 aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγερόμην</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγερέσθαι</span> (accented <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγέρεσθαι</span> by ancient grammarians), part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγρόμενος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">collect, call together,
            assemble;</span> pass. and aor. mid. <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">gather
            together;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐς φρένα θυμὸς ἀγέρθη</span>, ‘consciousness’
          (‘presence of mind,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 4.152</span></i>), ‘was
          restored.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
